Why is stretching useful?

Stretching is excellent for relieving neck and back pain. And, in some cases, it can even replace taking pain relievers.

And, if you practice regularly, you can get rid of the pain completely.

Stretching relieves muscle tension and relieves the body of associated stress.

latestPosts.caption:
Something beautiful is rising in Greenwich Village…

After months of dreaming, designing, and building - our newest Yoga Space studio is slowly getting ready to open its doors. 

Light-filled rooms. Natural textures. Quiet corners made for deep breaths and soft landings.

We are opening our 4th location in Greenwich Village this summer. We can’t wait to welcome you into this next chapter with us. Stay close for more updates! 🤎✨

What feature are you hoping to see in our newest studio? 💭

We are happy to announce the return of a tender and gentle yoga class! 🤰🏻💕

Prenatal Yoga is a supportive, anatomy-based practice designed for your changing body and growing heart. With breathwork and intentional movement, we bring awareness to the pelvic floor and abdominal muscles, and build strength where it matters most.

Catered to the unique needs of this journey, prenatal yoga offers a safe space to build tolerance for discomfort, develop trust in both body and baby, and foster community as you prepare for birth and beyond.

Every Tuesday at 10:30am at Williamsburg. 

We invite you to join this very special class. Reservation link in bio! Send this to a soon-to-be mom🕊

latestPosts.caption:
June came in full and fast - just how seasonal shifts tend to do! 🌼

We moved from spring into summer, and you can feel the shift in vibe at the studio! We hosted two beautiful workshops - Sound & Stillness with @ilanalieberman and Pelvic Floor & Core with @thenatalizer - celebrated Pride Month with love and color, and welcomed our first heart-filled collab with @jamiesfarmnewyork, who brought sweet treats to our LIC community. ✨

A month of movement, new faces, and fresh beginnings… and there’s still more to come. This summer brings more workshops to help you slow down and root in - and the opening of our Greenwich studio is just around the corner. 🌿

Wishing you a fun and exciting July! 🌞💫

latestPosts.caption:
Happy Pride! 🌈 Flowing through this practice with gratitude, strength, and self-love. Yoga teaches us to honor who we are and shows us the power of showing up as your full, authentic self - on and off the mat. 

This month we celebrate love, authenticity, and the freedom to be ourselves. Love is love, always. ❤️✨

When the world feels loud or your thoughts get tangled, the mat becomes a sanctuary - a place to find peace and clarity.

It’s more than just movement - it’s an invitation to rest, release, and reconnect with yourself. No pressure. No expectations.

Stepping onto the mat is like magically hitting the reset button on yourself 🕊️✨

Every day we are grateful for yoga but especially today. Happy International Yoga Day! 🌎✨

Today, we honor yoga’s ancient roots and the global impact this practice has. It’s a reminder of how yoga quietly connects us - to our breath, to each other, and to this one beautiful Earth we share. 🌿

This year’s theme, “Yoga for One Earth, One Health,” is a gentle reminder: that personal health and environmental health are deeply connected. When we care for our bodies and well-being through yoga, we care for the planet too. 

So tell us - what has yoga brought into your life? 💛
 Send this to your yoga buddy or teacher and spread the yoga love today! 🕊️

#InternationalYogaDay #OneEarthOneHealth

Happy Summer YS fam! 🌞🌞 It’s officially Summer today — and we’re feeling it with this week’s warm weather and the energy you’ve been bringing into the studios! 

The solstice arrives tonight at 10:42 PM, marking the start of a new season and the longest day of the year in NYC. Soak up every drop of sunlight you can and make sure to stay cool and hydrated in this heat!

Here’s to a season full of sunshine, connection, movement — and most of all, joy! Let’s make it one to remember 💛

What are you looking forward to this summer?

Breathe, baby, breathe—your body has done something incredible — now let’s help it FEEL incredible too. ✨

Join me at @yogaspace.nyc for a pelvic floor + core workshop designed to help you move with more joy, strength, and confidence in your new body.

🗓️ Sunday, June 29th 3:30-4:30pm

We’ll start with the foundation: 360° breathing, your body’s built-in reset button. Then we’ll gently layer in movement that reconnects you to your core, supports your pelvic floor, and helps you feel AWESOME again — not just physically, but emotionally, too.

Because this isn’t about “bouncing back.”
It’s about moving forward — with love, power, and a whole lotta breath.

👶 Perfect for pregnant and postpartum moms
🧘‍♀️ Beginner-friendly, safe, and deeply supportive
🌈 All are welcome — this is for anyone who wants to strengthen their core and pelvic floor

👉 Limited spots! Sign up through the link in bio.

Come as you are. Leave feeling stronger from the inside out. 💗

latestPosts.caption:
Pregnant, postpartum, or just want to feel more connected to your core? This one’s for you. 💛

Power From Within is a supportive, practical workshop to help you safely strengthen your core and pelvic floor - the foundation of your strength, balance, and ease. Designed with pregnancy and postpartum in mind, but open to all, this workshop is perfect if you’re looking to relieve back pain, reduce incontinence, or just move through life with more support.

Led by our amazing @thenatalizer - pre & postnatal coach and fellow mama - you’ll get evidence-based tools, gentle movement, and real talk about what your body needs right now.

✨ Sunday, June 29 | 3:30–4:30PM 📍Yoga Space Greenpoint 🔗 Space is limited - reserve your spot via link in bio

No pressure. No shame. Just care, community, and connection. 🌿
